## Proposed Update

**File:** `.claude/agents/developer.md`
**Section:** CODE READABILITY (after Function Size)
**Type:** Add

### After:

```markdown
### Control Flow

- Prefer early returns over nested conditionals
- Use guard clauses to handle edge cases first
- Maximum 2 levels of nesting; extract functions if deeper

**Example:**

```typescript
// BAD: nested conditionals
const processUser = (user: UserT) => {
  if (user) {
    if (user.isActive) {
      if (user.hasPermission) {
        return doSomething(user);
      }
    }
  }
  return null;
};

// GOOD: early returns
const processUser = (user: UserT) => {
  if (!user) return null;
  if (!user.isActive) return null;
  if (!user.hasPermission) return null;

  return doSomething(user);
};
```
```

**Rationale:** Reduces cognitive load, matches existing project guidelines in CLAUDE.md

